Some of these pages really need to be reordered...
There's some scene transitions, particularly with Mike and Evals' gender adventures, that are really sudden, because they're just sorta randomly scattered throughout the chapter.
So like, on the left page, you have Alabaster saying Keith has "ONE HOUR!" and then on the right, it's Heartbutt Mike.
And it's like, wow, this is sudden, since it's the first time Mike's shown up in the book.
Yeah, so I'm just going to move that page and the next one with Mike and Evals to a good transition point a few pages back.
It's a very minor sort order and doesn't change the order of events any.
I go through and I check to see which pages end up on the left and right
I try to make sure it flows well
It's way easier to get away with transitions online since it's 1 page at a time
One thing I try very hard to make sure, is that when there's something dramatic happening, it happens after a pageturn.
So it's like "And then suddenly!" and then you have to turn the page to see Adelaide appear in the courtroom, or the tower blow up, etc
Or like if there's a flashback, I like to have it start on the left page. So that both left and right pages are black bordered.
Luckily, since a lot of stuff is going on at once, usually, and there's just one-off pages with Mike and Evals or whatever, it's very easy to just shift one page without changing the order of events.
And I only do that if absolutely necessary for a dramatic reveal or whatever.

Tiger society mostly consists of tigers.
Tiger society isn't completely formed yet.
But it's very class-based. There's a lot of emphases on class and social structure.

There are a lot of nomadic caravans that make up the smaller classes, and one major city that is very impressive and surrounded by waterfalls.

Tigers are extremely vain about fur patterns, and whites are considered extremely blessed.

Fortune telling and superstition is huge. Tigers "read" stripes, and some patterns are very unlucky and can doom some tigers.
Some tigers are quite strange. There are groups that shave their bodies to look more like humans.
